---
export const prerender = true;
import SiteScripts from '../components/SiteScripts.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>About Orient — the shared meaning layer for humans and machines</title>
<meta name="description" content="Orient turns organisational knowledge into a living meaning graph — used by people to think and communicate, and by machines to act with context, evidence, memory, and restraint." />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/orient.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/about.css?v=3" />

{import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID && (
  <>
    <script async src={`https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=${import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID}`}></script>
    <script is:inline define:vars={{ gaId: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID }}>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', gaId);
    </script>
  </>
)}

<SiteScripts />
</head>
<body class="ab-page">

<!-- ============ HEADER ============ -->
<header class="site-header" id="header">
  <div class="wrap bar">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo" />
    </a>
    <nav class="site-nav">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="#top" aria-current="page" style="color:var(--ink)">About</a>
    </nav>
    <button class="btn" data-scroll="#access">Request access</button>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="top">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="ab-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">About Orient</span>
      <h1>We build the shared meaning layer for humans <em>and</em> machines.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Orient turns the work people create into a living <b>meaning graph</b> — used by teams to think and communicate, and by agents to act with <b>context, evidence, memory</b>, and restraint.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ PROBLEM ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-problem">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="lead">Companies are deploying more copilots, assistants and agents than ever — and <span class="hl">assume those systems understand the business.</span> <span class="mut">They don't.</span></p>
      <p class="sub">Most AI relies on retrieval: it searches files, pulls chunks, and generates plausible answers. But organisations don't run on chunks. They run on meaning — what's true, what's supported, what's contested, what's already been decided, what's stale, and what's safe to act on.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ THESIS ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-thesis">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p>Humans feed the graph. Machines act from it. Orient keeps both working from the <span class="em">same understanding</span>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ STORY BLOCKS ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-story">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="ab-block">
        <div class="lbl">Why we built Orient</div>
        <div>
          <h2>They can act before they understand.</h2>
          <p>We built Orient after watching AI tools generate, search and summarise across organisations — without knowing what the company actually believes, what evidence supports a claim, what has already been decided, or what should never be said. Output accelerated; <b>shared understanding did not.</b></p>
          <p>Our background spans reasoning systems, language models, agentic architectures, optimisation and vision — the cutting edge of applied AI. Across every domain the gap was the same: machines could act, but had no organisational meaning to act from. Orient is our answer to that gap.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ab-block">
        <div class="lbl">Two connected products</div>
        <div>
          <h2>One graph. People and agents.</h2>
          <p><b>Orient for Humans</b> is a thinking and communication space where teams capture knowledge, ask questions, resolve answers, create frames, share understanding, and build organisational memory.</p>
          <p><b>Orient for Machines</b> is a machine-ready meaning layer that lets agents, assistants, copilots and workflows consume that resolved knowledge, context, frames, and memory — with evidence and safe-to-act signals attached.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ab-block">
        <div class="lbl">Who this is for</div>
        <div>
          <h2>Organisations operating in complexity.</h2>
          <p>Orient is for companies where strategy, decisions, research and communication move across many teams, formats and stakeholders — and where agents and AI workflows now need that organisation's meaning to act safely.</p>
          <ul class="ab-for">
            <li>Leadership and strategy teams</li>
            <li>Product, research and cross-functional organisations</li>
            <li>Teams deploying <span>copilots, agents and AI workflows</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ USE CASES ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-cases">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow clay">Use cases</span>
        <h2>Land with humans. Expand to machines.</h2>
        <p>Orient starts where knowledge is complex and decisions matter — then opens the same resolved meaning to the agents and workflows that act on it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ab-cases-grid reveal">
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">01</div>
          <h4>Strategy &amp; Leadership</h4>
          <p>Resolve strategic questions, frame the direction and prepare board narratives. Machine layer: executive briefings, strategy agents, decision memory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">02</div>
          <h4>Product Launch &amp; Positioning</h4>
          <p>Resolve the narrative, approved claims and launch frames. Machine layer: sales and support agents, product copilots, safe generation from approved claims.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">03</div>
          <h4>Board &amp; Investor Prep</h4>
          <p>Prepare decks, investor narratives, Q&amp;A and risk views. Machine layer: board-prep agents, follow-up tracking, unresolved-assumption monitoring.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">04</div>
          <h4>Sales &amp; Approved Claims</h4>
          <p>Resolve positioning, proof points and objection handling. Machine layer: proposal agents, call-prep copilots, approved-claim and safe-to-say checking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">05</div>
          <h4>Research-to-Action</h4>
          <p>Capture material, surface contradictions and create decision-ready frames. Machine layer: research agents, open-probe queues, synthesis agents.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">06</div>
          <h4>Agent Grounding</h4>
          <p>Give every agent the organisation's resolved context, evidence, memory and safe-to-act signals — so they act with restraint, not guesswork.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ MISSION ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-mission reveal">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="pre">Our mission is to give every organisation one resolved source of what's true, decided and safe to act on — a living meaning graph that people think with and machines act from, where you can measure whether understanding actually held.</p>
      <blockquote>The next advantage isn't producing more. It's people and agents working from the <span class="em">same understanding</span>.</blockquote>
      <div class="attr">The Orient Team · The shared meaning layer for humans and machines</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CONTACT ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-contact">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="ab-contact-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="role">Visit Orient</div>
          <h2>Stockholm.</h2>
          <address>
            Orient<br />
            Malmskillnadsgatan 32<br />
            111 51 Stockholm<br />
            Sweden
          </address>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="role">Contact</div>
          <p class="who"><b>Mikael Larsson</b></p>
          <p class="who"><a href="mailto:mikael@orientos.ai">mikael@orientos.ai</a></p>
          <p class="note">Reach out about demos, partnerships, press, or whether Orient is a fit for your organisation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CLOSING CTA ============ -->
  <section class="closing" id="access">
    <div class="wrap">
      <img src="/logomark.svg" alt="" class="closing-mark" />
      <h2>Work from the same understanding.</h2>
      <p>Orient is the meaning layer beneath your team and its agents — one resolved source of what's true, decided and safe to act on. Request access to the platform.</p>
      <form class="waitlist onink" data-waitlist data-success="On the list ✓" style="justify-content:center">
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@company.com" aria-label="Work email" required />
        <button class="btn" type="submit">Request access</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
<Newsletter />
<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo-light.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo footer-logo" />
    </a>
    <div class="line">A meaning operating system for humans and machines.</div>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="#top">About</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<script is:inline src="/landing.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
